<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-66521B0A-9EE4-432D-8C42-473926C9FB43" version="1" lang="en-US"?><task xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-66521B0A-9EE4-432D-8C42-473926C9FB43" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic task)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c task oceTask-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic task/task "><title class="- topic/title ">How to request a license via ORS</title><abstract class="- topic/abstract " id="M148553-B105"><p class="- topic/p ">It is possible to get a license through On Remote Service (ORS) (instead of making the license request and retrieving the valid license manually). 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">This document describes the procedure: 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">How it works: 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Once there is an agreement up-front with the customer regarding the license(s) requested, a Product license number is registered in ILMS database. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">At printer installation time: 
</p><ol class="- topic/ol "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Service enters the 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Product license</b> number via Settings Editor 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Service makes a request on Settings Editor with one single button which will send automatically all the required information to the back-office (Data Request Server also known as DRS) via ORS 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> ORS will transmit this information to ILMS server which will build the valid license 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> If everything is OK: after a couple of minutes the valid license will be available at the back-office and the controller which connects to the back-office every 5 minutes will retrieve it automatically. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Service needs to install the valid license, which is now available on the controller via the Settings Editor. 
</p></li></ol></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Installation</category></metadata></prolog><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><section id="GUID-D3A825A6-4EC3-4E19-AEA5-A298CC09165D" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "> Preparation</title><table id="GUID-42BA930E-DBF2-4F1C-8EAC-0F409ABC8266" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="2" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="10*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="90*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> In case of an initial installation, a product license must be known. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> In case of an upgrade the product license must already be present. 
</p><fig id="GUID-7830D57C-68DB-4704-A5A6-296C44DAF3D7" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title ">Example screen</title><image href="GUID-75C248BC-BA1A-4721-84A0-A86692E3A61D-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-75C248BC-BA1A-4721-84A0-A86692E3A61D-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p "> A product license (representing the customer) must have been communicated by the order management or the Software Fulfilment to the Field Service Technician. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> This product license takes into account the agreement made up front with the customer on the licenses request (Base license + requested optional(s)). 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">ORS must be enabled and active. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">This can be checked on the operator panel. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">On the operator panel, select: System / Remote services/ Remote Connection and check/update: 
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Remote connection status: "Connected" 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Remote connection: "Enabled" 
</p></li></ul><fig id="GUID-6776B943-50ED-479C-BFC3-4AAD14496F83" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-7DBA95FC-5C6C-4148-9673-16E3C004A3E5-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-7DBA95FC-5C6C-4148-9673-16E3C004A3E5-low.png"/></fig><note id="GUID-519F2F70-7430-40BC-96A6-2652D6C157F4" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p "> If required: Setup the Proxy settings. See 
<xref keyref="ORSSETUP001" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-07BC7664-5AAE-4C27-A331-C2F6D4AB2349.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text How to set up On Remote Service (ORS)?>How to set up On Remote Service (ORS)</xref>. 
</p></note></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="GUID-6A6A9A31-0D05-49C0-A721-CDB495E91CD1" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "> License request</title><table id="GUID-B9384D85-5FC6-4F23-9A60-125F52569ED5" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="2" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="10*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="90*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Make sure that the product license contains the product license for this customer. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> In case the product license is empty, fill out the product license. 
</p><note id="GUID-4687375B-27BC-40E8-8238-4E8A01105BAF" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p "> Without the product license the request will fail. 
</p></note><fig id="GUID-82618E5D-0141-4C50-86AD-08FEBB551815" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title ">Example screen</title><image href="GUID-75C248BC-BA1A-4721-84A0-A86692E3A61D-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-75C248BC-BA1A-4721-84A0-A86692E3A61D-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Click on request activation to send the dongle information and product license to the back-office system 
</p><fig id="GUID-BABE3B1E-5C62-4435-A47D-51309C8A91FD" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title ">Example screen</title><image href="GUID-65859BB1-C385-414F-B5D7-286A204A0D0D-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-65859BB1-C385-414F-B5D7-286A204A0D0D-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Click on the "Request activation" button to send the request. 
</p><fig id="GUID-808818A2-4EC0-40C5-A810-8400A20D705C" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-2345474C-0DBE-4F5F-8049-269B52B4A241-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-2345474C-0DBE-4F5F-8049-269B52B4A241-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">4 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> The result of the request is shown. When clicking "OK" the window will disappear. 
</p><fig id="GUID-7849C51F-1D98-4510-BB39-4B4A74F47B16" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-AE63D87C-4B04-4F9F-9980-33AE0442D242-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-AE63D87C-4B04-4F9F-9980-33AE0442D242-low.png"/></fig></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-7D3F358C-1AB9-4A5D-9B0E-C75D689F152E.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Installation</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
